      "code_changes": [
        {
          "content": "{\n  \"symbols\": [\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"apache/kafka\",\n      \"path\": \"clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/server/authorizer/Authorizer.java\",\n      \"symbol\": \"Authorizer\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"apache/kafka\",\n      \"path\": \"clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/server/authorizer/AuthorizerServerInfo.java\",\n      \"symbol\": \"AuthorizerServerInfo\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"apache/kafka\",\n      \"path\": \"clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/server/authorizer/Action.java\",\n      \"symbol\": \"Action\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"apache/kafka\",\n      \"path\": \"clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/errors/AuthorizerNotReadyException.java\",\n      \"symbol\": \"AuthorizerNotReadyException\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"apache/kafka\",\n      \"path\": \"clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/security/auth/KafkaPrincipal.java\",\n      \"symbol\": \"KafkaPrincipal\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"apache/kafka\",\n      \"path\": \"core/src/main/scala/kafka/server/AuthHelper.scala\",\n      \"symbol\": \"AuthHelper\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"apache/kafka\",\n      \"path\": \"core/src/main/scala/kafka/server/AclApis.scala\",\n      \"symbol\": \"AclApis\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"apache/kafka\",\n      \"path\": \"core/src/main/java/kafka/server/builders/KafkaApisBuilder.java\",\n      \"symbol\": \"KafkaApisBuilder\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"text\": \"ACL Authorization classes and interfaces found in Apache Kafka repository:\\n\\nCore Interface Definitions (clients/src/main/):\\n1. Authorizer.java (org.apache.kafka.server.authorizer.Authorizer) - Defines the main pluggable Authorizer interface. This interface defines methods for authorization (authorize), ACL management (createAcls, deleteAcls, acls), and server startup (start). It includes default implementations for authorizeByResourceType and aclCount methods. The interface extends Configurable and Closeable.\\n\\n2. AuthorizerServerInfo.java (org.apache.kafka.server.authorizer.AuthorizerServerInfo) - Defines an interface for runtime broker configuration metadata provided to authorizers during startup, including cluster resource, broker id, endpoints, inter-broker endpoint, and early start listeners.\\n\\nSupporting Classes (clients/src/main/):\\n3. Action.java (org.apache.kafka.server.authorizer.Action) - A utility class representing an authorization action with resource pattern, operation, resource reference count, and logging flags.\\n\\n4. AuthorizerNotReadyException.java (org.apache.kafka.common.errors.AuthorizerNotReadyException) - An exception class indicating the authorizer is not ready to receive requests yet. Extends RetriableException.\\n\\n5. KafkaPrincipal.java (org.apache.kafka.common.security.auth.KafkaPrincipal) - A utility class implementing Principal interface that represents a principal with type and name. Used for ACL authorization logic.\\n\\nCore Implementation/Usage Classes (core/src/main/):\\n6. AuthHelper.scala (kafka.server.AuthHelper) - A helper class that uses the Authorizer plugin. Implements various authorization methods including authorize, authorizeClusterOperation, authorizeByResourceType, partitionSeqByAuthorized, filterByAuthorized, and computeDescribeClusterResponse. Acts as a wrapper around the Authorizer interface.\\n\\n7. AclApis.scala (kafka.server.AclApis) - Handles ACL-related API requests (DescribeAcls, CreateAcls, DeleteAcls). Uses Option[Plugin[Authorizer]] and delegates to the authorizer plugin for ACL operations.\\n\\n8. KafkaApisBuilder.java (kafka.server.builders.KafkaApisBuilder) - A builder class for constructing KafkaApis instances with dependency injection. Contains a field for Optional<Plugin<Authorizer>> authorizerPlugin that is used during object construction.\"\n}\n",
